President Muhammadu Buhari has arrived Katsina en route Daura, his home town for a private visit. The Presidential Airforce One arrived the  Umaru Musa Yaradua International Airport at about 5.10pm. After airport pleasantries, President Buhari accompanied by Governor Aminu Masari boarded a Presidential Chopper to Daura, about 75km from Katsina town. On arrival in Daura, the President is expected to pay a condolence visit to the Emir of Daura Umar Faruk and Family of late Sen. Bukar Mustapha who died three days ago. Already security around the deceased residence have been beefed up ahead of  his arrival as security personnel  have condone the area turning away sympathisers and media men from access to the area. Late Sen Bukar has since been buried at Gabas cemetery after funeral prayers held at the Kangiwa Square located in front of the palace of the Emir of Daura, Umar Faruk. A special three-day prayers is expected to hold for the repose of his soul which President Buhari is expected to graced.